<p>I am using the following function to remove all extra white space from a string:</p>  <pre><code>CREATE FUNCTION RemoveSpaces ( -- ============================================= -- Author:      Amit Singh -- Description: Remove extra spaces from string -- Usage:       SELECT dbo.RemoveSpaces('Code  Jotter') -- =============================================     @str AS VARCHAR(MAX) ) RETURNS VARCHAR(MAX) AS BEGIN     RETURN     REPLACE(REPLACE(REPLACE(@str,' ','{}'),'}{',''),'{}',' ') END </code></pre>  <p>The function works fine. But when I try to use the function in a <code>SELECT</code> statement, the string remains intact.</p>  <pre><code>SELECT TOP 1       dbo.RemoveSpaces(sms_message)   FROM MyTable </code></pre>  <p>I receive the same value as <code>sms_message</code> without the extra spaces removed.</p>